article.description: The Seattle SuperSonics shot only 38 percent from the floor and 65 percent from the line and were outrebounded 51-45. Against the struggling Denver Nuggets, however, that was good enough.
article.headline: Mason, Payton carry Sonics on off night
article.linkText: Sonics don't shoot well but slip past Nuggets
article.story:
DENVER (AP) -- It could have been a disaster. The Seattle SuperSonics shot only 38 percent from the floor and 65 percent from the line and were outrebounded 51-45. Against the struggling Denver Nuggets, however, that was good enough. Desmond Mason scored 23 points and Gary Payton 21 as the SuperSonics handed the Nuggets their 10th straight loss, 79-77 on Monday night. "Tonight we got lucky,'' Payton said. "We should have won by more than that. But we're not making plays at the end, and we let them get too many rebounds.'' Mason had eight points in the third quarter and Kenny Anderson six points in the final period to help the Sonics hold off the Nuggets. Anderson finished with 12 points. "We shot the ball poorly pretty much all night,'' Seattle coach Nate McMillan said. "We found a way to get the lead and build a little lead going down the stretch. "Desmond and Gary pretty much carried the team the entire night. Mason stepped up and really played well. Kenny gave us some good minutes off the bench. The bench stepped up and played well.'' Anderson's jumper from the corner made it 73-67 with 2:13 left. After an exchange of baskets, Mason's two free throws gave Seattle a 79-73 lead with 7.2 seconds remaining. Denver rookie Nene Hilario scored on a dunk and was fouled with 4.8 seconds left. He missed the free throw, and Juwan Howard put back the rebound, cutting the lead to two. The Nuggets fouled Payton, who missed both free throws with 2.1 seconds left. Howard got the rebound, but his pass was intercepted by Mason. Hilario led Denver with 21 points, and Howard had 19 points and 15 rebounds. The Sonics were without their second-leading scorer, Rashard Lewis, who was sent back to the team hotel before the game, suffering from the flu. "I sound like a broken record,'' Nuggets coach Jeff Bzdelik said, "but we've got a lot of young players.'' At one point, the Nuggets had four rookies on the floor. "We outrebounded them, did a good job of getting to the line, we outscored them in the paint 44-22, we outscored them in second-chance points, we had more fast-break points,'' Bzdelik said. "Two things always seem to prevent us from winning. We had 21 turnovers to their 12, and we couldn't make shots.'' Denver shot 37 percent. Mason scored six points in an 8-0 spurt to start the third period, giving Seattle a 42-39 lead. Howard's turnaround jumper put Denver ahead 47-46, but the SuperSonics then went on a 13-3 run -- capped by Payton's 18-footer -- to close out the period with a 59-50 lead. Hilario had seven of Denver's first 11 points in the final period, and the Nuggets got within two points on four occasions. Denver erased a six-point deficit in the second quarter with a 17-2 flurry, including 11 straight points. Hilario's fast-break slam dunk started the spurt, and Howard followed with back-to-back three-point plays. Layups by Ryan Bowen and Junior Harrington and two free throws by Donnell Harvey gave the Nuggets a 39-30 lead. The Sonics cut it to 39-34 at intermission on Anderson's two free throws and Mason's short jumper. Seattle scored only nine points in the quarter -- a season low for any quarter -- on 3-of-22 shooting (.136).

Game notes
The teams will play back-to-back games, meeting again Friday in Seattle. ... Payton increased his career point total to 17,792, moving ahead of former Sonics player and coach Lenny Wilkens into 52nd place on the NBA's scoring list. ... Payton, who had nine assists, needs three more to pass Wilkens (7,211) for eighth on the NBA career assists list. ... The Nuggets have lost 15 of their last 16 games and five straight home games, the most since they moved into the Pepsi Center in 1999. ... Denver's reserves shot just 17 percent (4 for 23) and scored only 13 points.
